creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 136 by Various.
Read in English by J Korth; Son of the Exiles; DomBombadil; Shakira Searle; Ian King; Leonard Wilson; Bellona Times; filmmefatale; Winston Tharp; Bruce Kachuk; Algy Pug
This is a collection of 22 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for September 2014.
This collection includes the following: Blight, by Ralph Waldo Emerson The Bursting of the Boom, by Henry Lawson Edward Gray, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson Exiled, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Fall, leaves, fall, by Emily Brontë Finnigin to Flannigan, by Strickland W. Gillilan Give and Take, by John Gould Fletcher Gossamer, by Georgia Douglas Johnson Humouresque, by T. S. Eliot In The Servants' Quarters, by Thomas Hardy Mr. Apollinax, by T. S. Eliot An Old Woman of the Roads, by Pádraic Colum Roads, by Edward Thomas September, by Helen Hunt Jackson The Sign, by Edgar Lee Masters Solitude, by Alexander Pope The Taxi, by Amy Lowell Then Ag’in, by Sam Walter Foss To the Not Impossible Him, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Travel, by Edna St. Vincent Millay The Welsh Marches, by A. E. Housman Wild Winds, by Mary Franeis Butts For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (19MB)
